<subSubSection id="92407360CE108652D74D016F92852FC8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3756EE65262525C04FAE324D3636D7DD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="669F5C578AAD94FBF900F6DA5F215962" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Latin, 
<emphasis id="433ECA08C954D4272072B06AE11E809A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">isthmus</emphasis>
, Greek (
<normalizedToken id="99AC3E28D6AF684C55EB49EA26C7FAFF" originalValue="isthmós">isthmos</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="CAE63EC872E869912B94064013EAB022" originalValue="“neck”">&quot;neck&quot;</normalizedToken>
) meaning a narrow cellular structure that connects two larger bodies or cells, Greek, 
<emphasis id="D6AE13156F27C4993E437F569A25A3F8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">myces</emphasis>
, referring to fungus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="20D7DE5825B5873F56E13D736677880C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="94AD7587A53E9A99ADB0555F9B0E21A9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6442D09E51721360566B7EDCA306DA0B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Asexual morph hyphomycetous. 
<emphasis id="D523E6E8F69DC6482C4075B680F2E806" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mycelium</emphasis>
superficial and immersed. 
<emphasis id="3460F8CD4550DC90B80035E76145E880" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conidiophores</emphasis>
macronematous, mononematous, erect, unbranched, smooth, pale brown or hyaline, septate, sometimes reduced to conidiogenous cells. 
<emphasis id="E7B10EB39ACF1833990E24FC1F551FD6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
polyblastic, denticulate, integrated, terminal, sympodial extended. 
<emphasis id="878A5A8B5CEB000116E9D5E89A92B4DB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conidial secession</emphasis>
schizolytic. 
<emphasis id="E40582F6AFFD46F39B79C1D4FDFAC58C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conidia</emphasis>
acrogenous, isthmosporous, composed two cellular isthmic-segment obclavate, clavate, pyriform, obpyriform, lageniform, subulate fusiform to navicular to lanceolate, unicellular or septate, smooth, hyaline, connected by a very narrow, distinct or inconspicuous isthmus. Sexual state: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5504200096340572F87B658FA7E76CC3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type species">
<paragraph id="BBF2DAEB976BC67284B0B0A534BBAF68" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2BFBB381E92EFD924FB598564B10CEF8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="E13DD50C50F3324E5DBC4CF3B96DCD6C" authorityName="Z. F. Yu, M. Qiao &amp; R. F. Castaneda" authorityYear="2021" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Isthmomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Isthmomyces oxysporus" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="oxysporus">
<emphasis id="43ABE6ECAEB736A4E59DEDE42C64AE5D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Isthmomyces oxysporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Z.F. Yu, M. Qiao &amp; R.F. 
<normalizedToken id="A334E8E11104DC0439B211FCCE6E0A79" originalValue="Castañeda">Castaneda</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D39BF720BA2E69854B34E1BDE69F7CCA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="0E70FA4171C11F203EC7F13AE22AC7B1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C4333FCB217C990D272A8E7CD178D522" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="90CF8AA9AACF648FD405789BA29920F2" authorityName="Z. F. Yu, M. Qiao &amp; R. F. Castaneda" authorityYear="2021" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Isthmomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Isthmomyces" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="781EB533E7585B81E7CEB3F2B30396F2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Isthmomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="8ACE44CD91227E0DDC8BA299D0D78DE3" authorityName="Matsushima" authorityYear="1971" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Isthmolongispora" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Isthmolongispora" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C1F9556CC14F57C019E9FBCCE9F46816" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Isthmolongispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Matsush. in morphology. 
<taxonomicName id="83077E3C4909EF1C177AF0DE903C5A9A" authorityName="Matsushima" authorityYear="1971" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Isthmolongispora" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Isthmolongispora" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="57E985A3C965EEF6E12D12F270696D1F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Isthmolongispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was established with 
<taxonomicName id="071751B337AE6C0F254E358989C61B91" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="I." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="I. intermedia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="8EB7BD8A37D1D1E903F08286B10CA292" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Matsush. as type species (
<bibRefCitation id="CAEE6DCD4DD18A19603A3672C48BDAD2" author="Matsushima, T" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B28" refString="Matsushima, T, 1971. Microfungi from the Solomon Islands and Papua-New Guinea. Published by author, Kobe." title="Microfungi from the Solomon Islands and Papua-New Guinea. Published by author, Kobe." year="1971">Matsushima 1971</bibRefCitation>
). The genus is characterised by denticulate, sympodially-extending conidiogenous cells and isthmospore conidia made of two or several cellular structures, which are connected by very narrow isthmuses. In this study, specimens with two and more cellular isthmic-segments were collected, respectively. Phylogenetic analysis inferred from two loci showed that our isolates grouped together with 
<taxonomicName id="D15F8CEE23D0AFF70AFC973A9269512C" authorityName="Z. F. Yu &amp; R. F. Castaneda" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Z. F. Yu &amp; R. F. Castaneda" baseAuthorityYear="2021" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Isthmomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Isthmomyces lanceatus" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="lanceatus">
<emphasis id="1312D1672A8BFE1D5D0D1E42A7F24444" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Isthmomyces lanceatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="E22C3CE92FDD5C6FFF641E30F8393F22" authorityName="Qiao &amp; Zheng &amp; Guo &amp; Castañeda-Ruiz &amp; Xu &amp; Peng &amp; Zhang &amp; Yu" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Qiao &amp; Zheng &amp; Guo &amp; Castañeda-Ruiz &amp; Xu &amp; Peng &amp; Zhang &amp; Yu" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Isthmolongispora" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Isthmolongispora lanceata" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="lanceata">
<emphasis id="9B6BEF6EEC29E5B50AF9A9F8C421BB89" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Isthmolongispora lanceata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in 
<taxonomicName id="58A75EC9993E517A1A0577013675E887" authorityName="Matsushima" authorityYear="1971" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Isthmolongispora" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Microthyriaceae</taxonomicName>
. Combining morphological character and phylogenetic analysis, we finally erected the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="92D116E2601199632EBDC83410C90CE7" authorityName="Z. F. Yu, M. Qiao &amp; R. F. Castaneda" authorityYear="2021" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Isthmomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Isthmomyces" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="09A67DA7D51BD57E1C6E47696EB45EA2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Isthmomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to accommodate these isolates and 
<taxonomicName id="D0FEAC8F29F10A70E51179A76E96DE3A" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="I." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="I. lanceata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="lanceata">
<emphasis id="24C07FB05CE373CE997C76DA47CA4765" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. lanceata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
